00:40:27,220 --> 00:40:29,150
nice.

766
00:40:53,710 --> 00:40:55,880
Oh, yes!
You did it!
You did it!

767
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:58,780
[exclaims]

768
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:08,460
Oh, my God.
Alice is Frog #3!

769
00:41:08,500 --> 00:41:11,730
A frog?
What, I'm a frog?
Was I that bad?

770
00:41:11,770 --> 00:41:13,730
Well, no
offense, Alice,

771
00:41:13,770 --> 00:41:16,900
but you were
pretty awful.

772
00:41:16,940 --> 00:41:19,170
I thought
I sounded good.

773
00:41:19,210 --> 00:41:22,240
[chuckles]
Then you'd better
have your hearing checked,

774
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:25,080
'cause you didn't
sing one note right.

775
00:41:25,110 --> 00:41:27,240
Elizabeth,
was I that bad?

776
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:29,450
Well,

777
00:41:29,480 --> 00:41:31,580
you were
pretty awful.

778
00:41:33,520 --> 00:41:35,420
No.

779
00:41:45,370 --> 00:41:47,300
Al, can I come in?

780
00:41:53,210 --> 00:41:54,870
I, uh--

781
00:41:54,910 --> 00:41:56,040
I guess
you're still upset

782
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:59,280
about not
getting the part, huh?

783
00:41:59,310 --> 00:42:01,980
Kids are saying
I'm the worst
singer ever.

784
00:42:02,020 --> 00:42:05,520
Okay. So maybe
you're a little
tone deaf. So what?

785
00:42:07,750 --> 00:42:11,120
Wait. You knew that
I couldn't sing?
Well,

786
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:14,130
honestly, Alice, um,

787
00:42:14,160 --> 00:42:15,530
in the second grade,

788
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:17,660
you had a little trouble
carrying a tune.

789
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:22,170
Why didn't you tell me
that I stink?

790
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:24,370
Because I thought that
with a little practice,

791
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:25,800
when you got older
you'd be better.

792
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:27,440
You've ruined my life!

793
00:42:30,180 --> 00:42:33,910
It's not as bad as it seems.
I mean, in a few days,
no one will remember.

794
00:42:33,950 --> 00:42:36,410
I'll remember for
the rest of my life.

795
00:42:36,450 --> 00:42:40,180
I thought...
You're supposed
to help, Dad.

796
00:42:40,220 --> 00:42:42,050
It's bad enough that
I don't have a mom.

797
00:42:42,090 --> 00:42:43,890
Sometimes I feel like
I don't have a father either.

798
00:42:52,630 --> 00:42:54,600
[exhales]

799
00:42:54,630 --> 00:42:58,470
Hey. You want to
go out to dinner?
Your choice.

800
00:42:58,500 --> 00:43:01,340
Food is not
gonna help, Dad.

801
00:43:04,910 --> 00:43:06,240
Okay.

802
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:08,710
♪ Here I am ♪

803
00:43:08,750 --> 00:43:11,350
I'll be downstairs
if you need me.

804
00:43:11,380 --> 00:43:13,790
♪ Null and void ♪

805
00:43:17,090 --> 00:43:20,420
♪ And just
an empty shell ♪

806
00:43:22,500 --> 00:43:25,860
♪ Calling out to you ♪

807
00:43:25,900 --> 00:43:29,000
♪ So let me
take your hand ♪

808
00:43:31,070 --> 00:43:34,070
♪ And take me
where you will ♪

809
00:43:36,410 --> 00:43:41,310
♪ And help me understand ♪

810
00:43:41,350 --> 00:43:43,980
♪ 'Cause only you can make ♪

811
00:43:44,020 --> 00:43:47,120
♪ Something out of nothing ♪

812
00:43:47,150 --> 00:43:49,720
♪ Something out of ♪

813
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:51,990
♪ Me ♪

814
00:43:52,030 --> 00:43:55,060
I know I shouldn't
be mad at my dad,

815
00:43:55,100 --> 00:43:57,560
but why didn't
he tell me?

816
00:43:57,600 --> 00:44:00,430
Now I feel
worse than ever.

817
00:44:00,470 --> 00:44:04,700
I just really wish
my mom was here tonight.

818
00:44:04,740 --> 00:44:07,540
"Tom was a glittering
hero once more;

819
00:44:07,570 --> 00:44:10,510
"the pet of the old,
the envy of the young.

820
00:44:10,540 --> 00:44:13,540
"His name even went
into immortal print,

821
00:44:13,580 --> 00:44:15,650
"for the village paper
magnified him.

822
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:18,420
"There were some
that believed he would
be president yet,

823
00:44:18,450 --> 00:44:20,890
if he escaped hanging."

824
00:44:20,920 --> 00:44:23,520
[bell rings]

825
00:44:23,560 --> 00:44:27,930
Hey, Alice, did you hear
about your new nickname?
"Ribbit."

826
00:44:27,960 --> 00:44:30,390
[children laughing]
That's so funny!

827
00:44:40,370 --> 00:44:42,040
I thought you might
like to have this.

828
00:44:42,080 --> 00:44:43,340
You did a very good job,

829
00:44:43,380 --> 00:44:46,940
once you remembered
the assignment.

830
00:44:46,980 --> 00:44:50,950
Would've been an "A,"
but you turned it in late.

831
00:44:50,980 --> 00:44:54,550
You know,
everyone has their
own talent, Alice.

832
00:44:54,590 --> 00:44:57,690
And when you set your
mind to it, you have
quite a way with words.

833
00:44:59,490 --> 00:45:03,190
Thanks.
I heard about
the musical,

834
00:45:03,230 --> 00:45:06,800
and I'm sorry you didn't
get the part you wanted.

835
00:45:06,830 --> 00:45:09,000
I'm kind of glad
I have detention.

836
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:12,240
I'd rather be here than
have to face everyone.

837
00:45:13,640 --> 00:45:15,610
Tell you what.

838
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:18,210
Since you already
finished your report,

839
00:45:18,240 --> 00:45:21,280
why don't you help me
set up the bulletin board
for the Read-A-Thon?

840
00:45:21,310 --> 00:45:23,150
Okay.

841
00:45:23,180 --> 00:45:25,880
♪ I've dreamt this ♪

842
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:28,190
♪ I've longed this ♪

843
00:45:28,220 --> 00:45:32,460
♪ I've lived this
